==English==

===Etymology===
A name probably of Egyptian origin, signifying 'child'. From the root 'moseh' = 'emerge (from the water)'.

===Proper noun===
'''Moses'''

# A name from the [[Old Testament]]. Moses led the slaved Jews out of Egypt. Brother of [[Aaron]] in the Book of the [[Exodus]]
# A male [[given name]].

